The paper deals with a combinatorial optimization problem (Stochastic Matching) and proposes improved approximation algorithms for it. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) or Game Theory (cs.GT) sub-categories. Additionally, the problem has applications in kidney exchange and online dating, which suggests that it could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) or Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves probabilistic analysis and the use of random permutations, which suggests that it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
